   <title>Automated Functions for Log Rotation and Cleanup</title>
   <prolog>
      <source>ST4 ID: 16331007883</source>
      <permissions view="ericsson_internal"/>
      <metadata>
         <othermeta content="NA" name="workitem"/>
      </metadata>
      <resourceid id="NA"/>
   </prolog>
   <!--THIS TOPIC IS PART OF THE BESR REPO, DO NOT EDIT IT WITHOUT CONSULTING WITH DATA FLOW AREA TECHWRITERS!!!-->
   <conbody>
      <p>The Probe is shipped with the following additional functions. No manual configuration is needed on these functions.</p>
      <ul>
         <li>
                                    <p>Log rotation</p>
                                    <p>The <apiname>/etc/logrotate.d/cea-probe-logrotate</apiname> file is installed by the package. It configures the rotation of log files generated by the Probe components.</p>
                                 </li>
         <li>
                                    <p>Cleanup of old data files</p>
                                    <p>The <apiname>/etc/cron.hourly/cea-probe-cleanup</apiname> file is installed by the package. It configures the cleanup of old data files generated by the Probe components.</p>
                                 </li>
      </ul>
      <note id="note_N10055_N1002A_N10001" outputclass="st4mig_attention" type="note">
         <p>Do not edit these files. Package updates overwrite them automatically.</p>
      </note>
   </conbody>
</concept>